3
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,300
- Kwon? 
 - Yes.

4
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:39,567
Has there been any contact from Kang Hee?

5
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:43,033
A little while ago, she went up with ice cream.

6
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:45,400
- Kang Hee is here? 
 - Yes.

7
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:48,100
What's with the ice cream? She's not a child.

8
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,867
What about me? Did she bring any for me?

9
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:53,267
What?

10
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,000
So, Kang Hee has returned.

11
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:26,767
Why?

12
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:42,467
Wait.

13
00:01:42,467 --> 00:01:44,933
Is this Kang Hee's?

14
00:01:44,933 --> 00:01:47,667
Ji Chun Pil's daughter, Ji Kang Hee.

15
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,267
Open the door, please.

16
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:50,833
- Hide! Hide! 
 - Huh?

17
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:52,600
I told you to hide!

18
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:56,933
 Welcome drink prepared wholeheartedly for my daughter. 

19
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,767
Home sweet home.

20
00:01:58,767 --> 00:02:01,533
Open the door, will you, Kang Hee?

21
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:03,333
No, does it have to be now?

22
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:08,433
Please open the door. Your welcome drink has arrived.

23
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:12,500
 It's a beautiful day. Please open the door. 

24
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,560
Welcome to your sweet home!

25
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,800
This was your dad's dream.

26
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:22,633
A thoughtful dad dedicating this to his daughter.

27
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:28,667
It's locked.

28
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:32,633
 - Kang Hee, did you see the flowers in the vase?  
 - Yes.

29
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:36,167
While walking along the path,

30
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:38,833
 I found the wildflowers so beautiful, so I brought them for you. 

31
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:41,867
I just put them there for you…

32
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:46,833
Won't you open the door?

33
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:47,933
I'll go out.

34
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,500
Go out, where to? I'm outside now.

35
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,033
- I'll go out. 
 - Oh, my head.

36
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:55,567
Ah, sorry. I'm sorry, are you okay?

37
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,933
What's going on in your room?

38
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:02,933
 What could be there? How can you come unannounced like this? 

39
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:05,767
 How do you know who I'd be with? How can you just show up like this? 

40
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:07,200
- Were you with someone? 
 -  No.

41
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:09,333
It's not that I'm with someone, but what if I had been?

42
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,500
Ms. Kang Hee.

43
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,267
- You should've told me you were coming. 
 - Were you with someone?

44
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,633
No!

45
00:03:13,633 --> 00:03:14,867
Long time no see!

46
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:16,800
My goodness?

47
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,533
 Why is everyone coming to my room? 

48
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,900
Dad's like this, you know.

49
00:03:24,900 --> 00:03:29,067
The two of you talk comfortably.

50
00:03:29,067 --> 00:03:30,267
Thank you.

51
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:31,767
My room is here. Yes.

52
00:03:31,767 --> 00:03:33,800
Please go in and talk.

53
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,067
- Yes. 
 - Yes, yes.

54
00:03:35,067 --> 00:03:36,700
- Please go in. 
 - Then, I'll take a look at your room…

55
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,860
Let's go down and talk.

56
00:03:38,860 --> 00:03:40,430
Ah, come quickly.

57
00:03:40,433 --> 00:03:42,000
- He said go in… 
 - Where would you go uninvited?

58
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
This is driving me crazy.

59
00:03:58,033 --> 00:04:01,500
How could you make me hear from someone else that you're back in town?

60
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:05,267
People will think it's weird that your boyfriend doesn't know about these things.

61
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:08,933
 - Daughter. 
 - Why? 

62
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:10,900
 Hide! Hide! 

63
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,633
Why did I do that?

64
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:22,133
Right? You'll reflect on it, won't you?

65
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,233
I understand.

66
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:27,467
You wanted to give me a surprise, didn't you?

67
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:29,433
Will he be angry?

68
00:04:29,433 --> 00:04:32,067
Don't worry, I'm not angry.

69
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,860
Ms. Kang Hee.

70
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:40,260
Yes?

71
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:46,300
It's like the mood has changed a bit.

72
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:48,967
What has changed, exactly?

73
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:51,700
You've said all you had to, right?

74
00:04:58,033 --> 00:04:59,867
See you tomorrow.

75
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,900
 Can you be friends with me? 

76
00:05:57,833 --> 00:05:59,700
 I don't want to. 

77
00:06:30,867 --> 00:06:32,533
You went out.

78
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:39,700
Yes. I was just about to call.

79
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,333
Why?

80
00:06:43,367 --> 00:06:46,967
You first, you called.

81
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,733
Shall we meet for a moment?

82
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:56,267
Shall we?

83
00:06:56,267 --> 00:06:58,000
Now?

84
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,667
Now.

85
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:03,167
See you on the rooftop.

86
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:37,280
   

87
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:43,267
Can you be just friends with me?

88
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:49,367
- You can't, right? 
 - No, I can.

89
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:52,233
No. If you had thought of me as just a friend,

90
00:07:52,233 --> 00:07:54,667
why did you tell me to hide when your father came?

91
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,433
You could just say we ate ice cream together.

92
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:58,533
For fear of being misunderstood.

93
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:01,167
Okay, let's say that's the case.

94
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:04,700
But you and I can't be friends. We even kissed.

95
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,567
So what if we kissed once, does that make us something?

96
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:10,500
- How old-fashioned. 
 - You don't feel any way about the kiss?

97
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,200
You were the one who kissed, not me.

98
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,242
You liked it too, didn't you?

99
00:08:14,242 --> 00:08:16,100
You clung to it, saying it was good, and even embraced me.

100
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,467
What? Then, what is that?

101
00:08:17,467 --> 00:08:20,091
- I don't remember. 
 - You don't remember?

102
00:08:20,091 --> 00:08:22,625
So, do you remember everything every time you do it?

103
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:24,358
Every time?

104
00:08:25,854 --> 00:08:27,820
You must have done it a lot, huh?

105
00:08:28,485 --> 00:08:30,585
Of course.

106
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:35,967
Don't tell me you haven't done it once since then.

107
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,567
That time?

108
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,667
You remember that.

109
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,367
Honestly,

110
00:08:52,981 --> 00:08:56,448
if I had known you'd leave me, I wouldn't have slept with you then.

111
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,100
Kang Hee,

112
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:02,900
was it nothing to you?

113
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:08,433
To me, it's a memory I'll cherish for a lifetime.

114
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:10,600
Was it so insignificant and trivial to you?

115
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,625
Who said it was nothing?

116
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:15,092
It was my first time, too.

117
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:19,137
But what about it? After all this time.

118
00:09:19,137 --> 00:09:21,367
Once the construction is over, I'll leave Hana-eup.

119
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:23,967
And you'll live in this godforsaken place for the rest of your life.

120
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:26,193
I can leave now.

121
00:09:26,193 --> 00:09:28,618
If you're fine with it, I can follow you anywhere.

122
00:09:28,618 --> 00:09:30,043
I've told you so many times.

123
00:09:30,043 --> 00:09:31,976
But you didn't come.

124
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,000
After agreeing to go to Seoul with me,

125
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,533
you made me go alone.

126
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,100
You're right.

127
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,233
I'm sorry for that.

128
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:53,867
Because I regretted that,

129
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:58,000
I kept trying to come to you.

130
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:01,800
But you're the one who cut off contact and pushed me away.

131
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,000
Don't you think about my efforts?

132
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:09,633
Every time I barely reached out to you, you pushed me off the cliff.

133
00:10:12,467 --> 00:10:14,433
Let's stop this.

134
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:18,167
It's all in the past.

135
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,533
It's all bothersome.

136
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:26,633
Okay.

137
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:31,000
Let's stop this.

138
00:10:32,010 --> 00:10:34,920
   

139
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:04,340
   

140
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:51,600
   

141
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,300
Cheon Yeon Soo!

142
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,200
Ma'am, I need to wait, right?

143
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,267
Yes, please wait a moment.

144
00:12:41,267 --> 00:12:43,100
Huh? Unnie!

145
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,033
Ms. Nan Woo.

146
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,867
Director.

147
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:02,433
How can you and Esther manage to still be friends?

148
00:13:03,967 --> 00:13:06,400
Is this a situation of jealousy now? That kind of scenario?

149
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,067
I'm really just curious.

150
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:12,400
How can a man and a woman stay friends all their lives?

151
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,733
How do you do that?

152
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:17,233
- Was there never a crisis? 
 - A crisis?

153
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:20,833
Like, you both seeing each other as the opposite sex, for example?

154
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:23,833
Wow! Yes!

155
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:27,167
Kang Hee is finally starting to be curious about me.

156
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,400
No, that's not it…

157
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,400
Ugh, never mind, pretend you didn't hear it.

158
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:37,233
It's something that can be misunderstood, but...

159
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:39,767
we're just real friends.

160
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,133
- Let's make it 45 millimeters. 
 - Yes.

161
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,900
You placed the order for Rimadyl, right?

162
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,900
Ah, yes, I've checked it.

163
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,067
Next.

164
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,800
And…

165
00:13:58,433 --> 00:14:00,433
Huh? Unnie?

166
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:05,167
I felt cold while passing by. Can I have a cup of tea before I go?

167
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:07,533
Oh, of course! Chamomile, right?

168
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:08,433
Yes.

169
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:10,567
You'll have some too, right, boss?

170
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,500
Drink it and go.

171
00:14:37,533 --> 00:14:38,967
Boss, where are you going?

172
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,067
Veterinary visit.

173
00:14:40,067 --> 00:14:42,700
Where's the visit to?

174
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,067
There were no reservations today.

175
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:52,790
He left his scarf behind.

176
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:54,560
He'll be cold.

177
00:15:32,933 --> 00:15:34,933
Follow me to the rooftop.

178
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:39,733
Explain this.

179
00:15:39,733 --> 00:15:42,467
Why are you giving this back to me again?

180
00:15:42,467 --> 00:15:44,333
Are you disregarding someone's sincerity?

181
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:46,433
Give it to your boyfriend.

182
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,233
Stop right there.

183
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:51,667
If you don't accept this now, it's the end.

184
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:54,100
I won't be friends.

185
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,533
We're already over, aren't we?

186
00:15:56,533 --> 00:16:00,733
Wasn't it the end starting from when you dumped me at the hotel?

187
00:16:03,733 --> 00:16:06,800
Are you taking revenge on me right now?

188
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,867
 Drink this and go back. 

189
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:12,730
 - Drink it and go.  
 - I sent you a purple message.

190
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:14,630
You gave me chamomile and just left.

191
00:16:14,633 --> 00:16:18,467
 Give it to your girlfriend later. 

192
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,733
You're just mirroring the same wordsI said when I gave you the necklace.

193
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:23,700
Think whatever you want.

194
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:27,867
It's childish. So childish. Haven't you grown up at all?

195
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:29,067
Is it all about growing tall?

196
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:31,300
What about your heart not growing at all?

197
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,500
You weren't this childish even when you were younger.

198
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:37,133
You understood and accepted everything I did.

199
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,433
Mirroring.

200
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:49,600
Wow! Why is he like that, really?

201
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,400
 Manager. 

202
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:57,100
Yes, I'm coming.

203
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:59,167
Isn't it a bit different?

204
00:16:59,167 --> 00:17:02,533
This wall has a different size from the blueprint?

205
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:04,533
 Manager. 

206
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:06,967
I'm coming.

207
00:17:07,733 --> 00:17:11,167
The angle of this handrail doesn't match the original design.

208
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:15,133
 Manager. 

209
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:17,333
Almost there.

210
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:21,967
We need to select the electrical team before our team can enter.

211
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:30,400
Ah, my hands are shaking.

212
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:37,600
 - Manager. Manager, come out, over.  
 - Yes?

213
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,400
 To the first floor. 

214
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:48,167
Ms. Nan Woo called.

215
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:51,467
Unnie, a donkey is coming to our hospital.

216
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:53,567
We need to build a house urgently.

217
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:56,433
Could you help us?

218
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:02,267
Did Yeon Soo send you to ask me?

219
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:05,367
The director went to pick up the donkey.

220
00:18:05,367 --> 00:18:09,133
I'm just asking you for a favor.

221
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:16,500
Director.

222
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,800
I heard you were building a house for the donkey. Can you do it alone?

223
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,667
Really. What do you think a large animal veterinarian is?

224
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:27,067
Building houses for migratory birds and enclosures for wild animals is our specialty.

225
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:29,400
I'll help you.

226
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:30,900
It's okay.

227
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:31,967
   

228
00:18:31,967 --> 00:18:33,833
Many hands make light work.

229
00:18:33,833 --> 00:18:37,467
You know, they say, practice makes perfect.

230
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:41,367
Contrary to what I thought, I'm accustomed to the construction site.

231
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:47,400
Don't you think he'd be better than me?

232
00:19:13,867 --> 00:19:16,333
I thought building houses for wild animals was your specialty.

233
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:19,067
What wild animals did you build houses for, ants?

234
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:22,833
And you said you were used to the site's meals, so it seems that's all you've had.

235
00:19:22,833 --> 00:19:26,500
Besides, people can't build anthills.

236
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:34,867
Huh? Unnie!

237
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,567
What are you two doing right now?

238
00:19:37,567 --> 00:19:39,460
They've been like that since earlier.

239
00:19:39,460 --> 00:19:41,200
I wonder if they will end it today.

240
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:44,633
Wait! Did you cut that in the right size?

241
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:46,333
Hold on.

242
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:49,200
Did you cut this the wrong size?

243
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:55,667
We're already short on wood. What can we do if you mess it up like this?

244
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:57,867
You're really not helping.

245
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,233
No, there is plenty of wood.

246
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:02,467
Cheon Yeon Soo, you're going to build a fence. Right?

247
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,567
Let's go to the site together to load materials.

248
00:20:04,567 --> 00:20:06,200
Never mind, it's late.

249
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:09,133
If Kang Hee does it, it'll be done quickly. Come with me.

250
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:11,467
You can't just let anyone into the construction site.

251
00:20:13,033 --> 00:20:14,533
Car keys.

252
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,433
- Hurry up and give it to me. 
 - Hurry!

253
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,733
Please load this into the car.

254
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:33,933
- This one? 
 - Yes.

255
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:59,567
I'll do it. Load this up, please.

256
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:20,630
♫  There was some misunderstanding  ♫

257
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:23,067
Please install this here.

258
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,300
Can you install this for me?

259
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:30,550
♫  ...it is an awkward attraction  ♫

260
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:37,400
♫  Why do I end up thinking of you every night?  ♫

261
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:41,040
♫  What's clear is I'm putting in a lot of effort for you  ♫

262
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:44,150
♫  What's clear is I'm putting in a lot of effort for you  ♫

263
00:21:44,150 --> 00:21:47,860
