 So after all is said and done, money is the best… 

527
00:39:01,833 --> 00:39:05,667
 Sworn friends are the best, okay? 

528
00:39:06,367 --> 00:39:08,133
I remember now.

529
00:39:09,300 --> 00:39:12,067
You are Kang Hee's

530
00:39:12,067 --> 00:39:14,467
sworn friend, right?

531
00:39:14,467 --> 00:39:16,767
If you're Kang Hee's friend, you're my friend, too.

532
00:39:17,867 --> 00:39:19,533
Let's get along well.

533
00:39:28,033 --> 00:39:29,300
 Keep friends close… 

534
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:30,433
Ah, my head hurts.

535
00:39:30,433 --> 00:39:32,833
 And enemies closer. 

536
00:39:43,067 --> 00:39:44,533
See you.

537
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,400
You're not leaving?

538
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:53,467
Let's go to the construction site together. Because I have something to tell Kang Hee.

539
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,000
Is that so?

540
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,633
Let's go.

541
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:01,233
Haven't you seen the director?

542
00:40:01,233 --> 00:40:03,667
Hasn't he come to work today?

543
00:40:03,667 --> 00:40:08,633
- I called, but someone else answered. 
 - Another person?

544
00:40:08,633 --> 00:40:11,333
It was clearly the director's phone.

545
00:40:11,333 --> 00:40:14,200
"This is Geum Seok Kyeong." That's what they said.

546
00:40:21,367 --> 00:40:24,300
You two were together.

547
00:40:25,067 --> 00:40:26,800
Ms. Kang Hee,

548
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:29,800
Yeon Soo has something to tell you.

549
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:41,533
Did you drink? Both of you?

550
00:40:46,467 --> 00:40:47,967
Kang Hee.

551
00:40:49,333 --> 00:40:51,267
Kang Hee, we…

552
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:57,633
Let's be friends.

553
00:41:01,933 --> 00:41:04,933
I saw him with someone named Esther yesterday.

554
00:41:05,533 --> 00:41:07,233
It looked nice.

555
00:41:17,700 --> 00:41:19,567
Ah, it looks so good.

556
00:41:19,567 --> 00:41:23,200
Let's go through life together, as friends.

557
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:24,700
Okay?

558
00:41:31,833 --> 00:41:33,767
Welcome.

559
00:41:33,767 --> 00:41:35,367
Ms. Yoon Nan Woo?

560
00:41:35,367 --> 00:41:37,667
Yes, it's me.

561
00:41:39,667 --> 00:41:41,867
Goodbye.

562
00:41:52,067 --> 00:41:55,800
   

563
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,867
The director?

564
00:41:59,667 --> 00:42:02,767
I didn't know the director had this side.

565
00:42:02,767 --> 00:42:05,500
Did Yeon Soo really give this to you?

566
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:10,567
You said you were coming for advice, but you came to show off?

567
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:17,133
It wasn't just a bouquet, there were also concert tickets.

568
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,867
It is a boast, indeed.

569
00:42:20,867 --> 00:42:23,133
It's not going to be free.

570
00:42:23,133 --> 00:42:24,800
Buy me a meal.

571
00:42:27,067 --> 00:42:29,367
Do you know the title of the performance?

572
00:42:29,367 --> 00:42:31,067
What is it?

573
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:37,533
   

574
00:42:37,533 --> 00:42:41,633
Hey, isn't this a proposal?

575
00:42:43,133 --> 00:42:45,567
Exactly.

576
00:42:45,567 --> 00:42:47,700
Why are you reacting like this?

577
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:54,233
The director… You know he had a crush on Kang Hee, right?

578
00:42:54,967 --> 00:43:00,267
But he recently gave up on that. Very recently.

579
00:43:00,267 --> 00:43:02,567
Could it be the director…

580
00:43:02,567 --> 00:43:06,800
In a fit of anger, "oh well, whatever", and bam!

581
00:43:07,567 --> 00:43:10,300
I might cause a scene.

582
00:43:12,767 --> 00:43:16,400
What if I am that "anyone"?

583
00:43:17,267 --> 00:43:18,833
Nan Woo,

584
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:21,833
Yeon Soo is not like that.

585
00:43:21,833 --> 00:43:25,367
After dating all this time, you don't know what kind of person Yeon Soo is?

586
00:43:29,233 --> 00:43:31,233
Actually…

587
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:38,200
Did you hear anything from the director, by any chance?

588
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:43,000
Hey, with such a clear confession, what else do you need to confirm?

589
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:46,433
Is that so?

590
00:43:46,433 --> 00:43:48,133
Don't worry.

591
00:43:48,133 --> 00:43:51,433
Ugh, I can't listen to this out of jealousy.

592
00:43:51,433 --> 00:43:54,033
I'm going out first. Take your time.

593
00:44:08,233 --> 00:44:09,633
Hello!

594
00:44:09,633 --> 00:44:11,433
- Yes, hello! 
 - Hello!

595
00:44:11,433 --> 00:44:13,167
Why did you bring so much?

596
00:44:13,167 --> 00:44:14,800
Just a moment.

597
00:44:18,767 --> 00:44:21,367
- What's the occasion? 
 - Field trip.

598
00:44:22,267 --> 00:44:23,967
Why here?

599
00:44:23,967 --> 00:44:27,367
This is the real world. This is the real deal.

600
00:44:32,833 --> 00:44:34,633
Tastes… delicious.

601
00:44:39,500 --> 00:44:43,300
Yeon Soo gave flowers to Nan Woo.

602
00:44:45,133 --> 00:44:49,967
Yeon Soo too, and even Kang Hee.

603
00:44:50,667 --> 00:44:54,033
I do get jealous that everyone is dating.

604
00:44:57,667 --> 00:45:00,233
Ah, right. You have to work, don't you? I'm going now.

605
00:45:00,233 --> 00:45:02,100
You should do it, too.

606
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:04,533
You have a lot of blind dates.

607
00:45:35,567 --> 00:45:38,033
Mom, why aren't you answering the phone?

608
00:45:38,033 --> 00:45:41,333
Huh? Wait, the phone?

609
00:45:41,333 --> 00:45:43,933
Did you really send it? A bouquet to Ms. Yoon?

610
00:45:43,933 --> 00:45:46,667
Did she get it? Isn't it pretty?

611
00:45:46,667 --> 00:45:48,433
I spent some money.

612
00:45:48,433 --> 00:45:50,100
Why did you do that? I told you not to.

613
00:45:50,100 --> 00:45:51,900
Oh, really.

614
00:45:51,900 --> 00:45:54,267
At times like this, it makes me wonder if you're really my son.

615
00:45:54,267 --> 00:45:57,033
How can you not understand the heart of a woman?

616
00:45:57,767 --> 00:46:01,667
You two just need to score a goal in marriage now.

617
00:46:01,667 --> 00:46:05,867
There's no goalkeeper. You just have to kick it and it's a goal.

618
00:46:05,867 --> 00:46:07,733
Why don't you do it?

619
00:46:07,733 --> 00:46:11,300
Just let Yeon Soo take care of it himself.

620
00:46:11,300 --> 00:46:13,300
The kid just outright hates the idea.

621
00:46:13,300 --> 00:46:16,080
No, they did the dating on their own.

622
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:18,100
I have to help with the marriage.

623
00:46:18,100 --> 00:46:20,767
No one has the experience I do when it comes to marriage.

624
00:46:20,767 --> 00:46:25,700
There's a reason companies prefer experienced people.

625
00:46:27,467 --> 00:46:29,933
You got the play tickets, right?

626
00:46:29,933 --> 00:46:32,000
You can propose at the performance.

627
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:33,567
What?

628
00:46:33,567 --> 00:46:35,500
Ah, don't be nervous.

629
00:46:35,500 --> 00:46:39,733
After the play, when they call your names, just the two of you go out.

630
00:46:39,733 --> 00:46:41,400
You just have to do as they say.

631
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:44,200
- No, Mom! 
 - Yeon Soo.

632
00:46:44,200 --> 00:46:48,633
I can't get married before you again, can I?

633
00:46:48,633 --> 00:46:51,300
You have to do it quickly. So I can, too.

634
00:46:51,300 --> 00:46:54,800
Again? Hey, you're doing it again?

635
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:57,567
I mean, there's someone I'm interested in.

636
00:46:57,567 --> 00:47:01,233
If I like what you do, I'll ask for a proposal like that, too.

637
00:47:01,233 --> 00:47:03,767
Hey! Then, you'd have to request the story.

638
00:47:03,767 --> 00:47:05,367
I don't know.

639
00:47:05,367 --> 00:47:07,000
Yeon Soo!

640
00:47:10,033 --> 00:47:12,467
You're only a mother by name?

641
00:47:12,467 --> 00:47:15,100
How do you just keep on getting married without a break?

642
00:47:15,100 --> 00:47:17,367
There must be someone out there...

643
00:47:18,033 --> 00:47:21,567
who doesn't wander and only likes me.

644
00:47:23,333 --> 00:47:25,267
Are you looking for something?

645
00:47:25,267 --> 00:47:27,900
Ah, um… some flowers…

646
00:47:27,900 --> 00:47:30,233
I'm thinking of buying…

647
00:47:32,167 --> 00:47:35,467
Just give me the most expensive ones.

648
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,667
For your girlfriend?

649
00:47:41,667 --> 00:47:43,967
No, it's not.

650
00:47:43,967 --> 00:47:46,567
- I'll help you with the payment. 
 - Yes.

651
00:47:49,567 --> 00:47:54,200
   

652
00:48:20,060 --> 00:48:25,750
♫  Sometimes, when you spare me a gaze  ♫

653
00:48:25,750 --> 00:48:32,440
♫  as if it's a part of your every day  ♫

654
00:48:33,290 --> 00:48:40,633
♫  Without a word, you grab my hands  ♫

655
00:48:40,633 --> 00:48:42,267
Unnie!

656
00:48:44,767 --> 00:48:46,533
Is it your birthday?

657
00:48:46,533 --> 00:48:48,300
No.

658
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:49,367
Isn't it heavy?

659
00:48:49,367 --> 00:48:50,867
It's okay.

660
00:48:50,867 --> 00:48:54,267
It's the first gift from the director. I want to take it home myself.

661
00:48:54,267 --> 00:48:55,933
Cheon Yeon Soo?

662
00:48:56,833 --> 00:48:58,500
The flowers?

663
00:49:03,967 --> 00:49:06,733
Uh! Okay, then.

664
00:49:06,733 --> 00:49:08,900
Carry it carefully.

665
00:49:12,220 --> 00:49:18,990
♫  Please smile for me, I don't need anything else  ♫

666
00:49:18,990 --> 00:49:25,260
♫  Let me fill my eyes with you  ♫

667
00:49:25,260 --> 00:49:31,840
♫  Yes, please tell me, though my heart is still full  ♫

668
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:36,560
♫  of love for you  ♫

669
00:49:36,567 --> 00:49:41,570
   

670
00:49:47,300 --> 00:49:49,133
What are you doing?

671
00:49:53,767 --> 00:49:55,567
For me?

672
00:49:57,833 --> 00:49:59,600
Ah Reum.

673
00:50:03,967 --> 00:50:05,600
Or just throw it away.

674
00:50:05,600 --> 00:50:17,300
♫  I'm just full of fleeting worries, 
 so I'll just ask just in case  ♫

675
00:50:22,833 --> 00:50:26,167
- Is this your first time seeing a bouquet? 
 - Who are you giving it to?

676
00:50:26,167 --> 00:50:29,633
I received it, from a man.

677
00:50:30,667 --> 00:50:32,167
Hey!

678
00:50:32,900 --> 00:50:34,400
Cheon Yeon Soo,

679
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:38,600
you never bought me flowers even once.

680
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:40,267
You don't like flowers, do you?

681
00:50:40,267 --> 00:50:44,033
That's not true. I really like flowers.

682
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:47,033
- Should I buy them? 
 - No.

683
00:50:47,033 --> 00:50:48,967
It's too late.

684
00:50:48,967 --> 00:50:50,667
Just buy them.

685
00:50:50,667 --> 00:50:53,167
I will report it to Yoon Nan Woo right away.

686
00:50:53,167 --> 00:50:55,600
I can't even buy flowers for a friend?

687
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:57,333
Of course.

688
00:51:10,833 --> 00:51:15,200
Before starting the exterior work, please reinforce the scaffolding first.

689
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:16,533
Safety comes first.

690
00:51:16,533 --> 00:51:18,567
Oh, my! Rest assured.

691
00:51:18,567 --> 00:51:21,700
Everything will be ready before the person in charge arrives.

692
00:51:21,700 --> 00:51:23,500
Have a safe trip.

693
00:51:23,500 --> 00:51:26,867
I will go to the headquarters for the meeting and come back tomorrow.

694
00:51:26,867 --> 00:51:28,300
Okay. Understood.

695
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:30,067
You heard? Scaffolding reinforcement work.

696
00:51:30,067 --> 00:51:31,567
- Yes. 
 - Of course.

697
00:51:31,567 --> 00:51:34,000
All right, let's go then.

698
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,967
- The car keys. 
 - Ah.

699
00:51:37,300 --> 00:51:39,967
- Take care. 
 - Ah, then work hard.

700
00:51:39,967 --> 00:51:43,890
   

701
00:51:50,333 --> 00:51:52,040
   

702
00:52:09,667 --> 00:52:11,200
What is this?

703
00:52:13,000 --> 00:52:16,600
Let's just ride quietly.

704
00:52:19,833 --> 00:52:22,267
- Hey! 
 - It's not like I sat where I wanted, okay?

705
00:52:22,267 --> 00:52:24,633
This was the only seat available.

706
00:52:24,633 --> 00:52:26,367
Seatbelt.

707
00:52:42,367 --> 00:52:44,833
Let's just talk to each other on the way.

708
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:47,667
What did you say?

709
00:52:47,667 --> 00:52:50,267
I said let's just talk on the way.

710
00:52:50,767 --> 00:52:53,667
Is it okay to talk among friends?

711
00:52:53,667 --> 00:52:55,500
I'll allow it.

712
00:53:01,733 --> 00:53:04,233
Why are you going to Seoul?

713
00:53:04,233 --> 00:53:07,867
Just have some things to sort out, and you?

714
00:53:07,867 --> 00:53:09,833
My home has always been in Seoul.

715
00:53:09,833 --> 00:53:12,167
And my company is also in Seoul.

716
00:53:16,833 --> 00:53:18,733
How's life in Seoul?

717
00:53:19,533 --> 00:53:22,400
Right now, well… it's good.

718
00:53:23,367 --> 00:53:25,367
 Because of that guy? 

719
00:53:25,367 --> 00:53:29,600
Until I joined this company, it was really…

720
00:53:29,600 --> 00:53:31,867
What, how was it?

721
00:53:31,867 --> 00:53:34,200
It was like cursed hardtack.

722
00:53:34,200 --> 00:53:35,400
Hardtack?

723
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:37,100
Yeah.

724
00:53:37,100 --> 00:53:39,300
Do you remember the hardtack man?

725
00:53:39,967 --> 00:53:42,033
Yes, I remember.

726
00:53:45,767 --> 00:53:47,700
   

727
00:53:47,700 --> 00:53:50,567
We used to worry about it all the time.

728
00:53:50,567 --> 00:53:54,700
Worried the hardtack would get moist during the rainy season.

729
00:53:54,700 --> 00:53:58,100
Worried it would collect dust during the sand storm season.

730
00:53:58,100 --> 00:54:01,200
Worried it wouldn't sell in the midsummer.

731
00:54:01,200 --> 00:54:06,000
And then worried in the dead of winter that the man's hands would be cold.

732
00:54:10,233 --> 00:54:12,333
Life in Seoul is like that.

733
00:54:13,500 --> 00:54:16,500
Like rainy season hardtack,

734
00:54:16,500 --> 00:54:20,633
like summer hardtack, like winter hardtack.

735
00:54:59,067 --> 00:55:01,367
What does it matter, among friends?

736
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:06,567
No, I didn't sleep.

737
00:55:06,567 --> 00:55:08,500
You slept!

738
00:55:08,500 --> 00:55:10,767
Thought you were headbanging.

739
00:55:11,833 --> 00:55:14,367
Yeah, I slept.

740
00:55:14,367 --> 00:55:16,700
I owe you one.

741
00:55:16,700 --> 00:55:19,633
What? Should I compensate you?

742
00:55:20,500 --> 00:55:22,500
Sure.

743
00:55:22,500 --> 00:55:23,867
With what?

744
00:55:23,867 --> 00:55:25,800
A tour of Seoul.

745
00:55:26,700 --> 00:55:28,367
Please, do it for me.

746
00:55:30,567 --> 00:55:33,000
Ma'am, please come down carefully.

747
00:55:34,933 --> 00:55:37,467
- Over here! 
 - Oh dear, thank you.

748
00:55:37,467 --> 00:55:40,000
Not at all. Please go inside carefully.

749
00:55:44,067 --> 00:55:45,733
Is there a place you want to visit?

750
00:55:45,733 --> 00:55:47,233
Golden Gilt.

751
00:55:47,233 --> 00:55:49,333
Our company?

752
00:55:49,333 --> 00:55:50,467
Why there?

753
00:55:50,467 --> 00:55:51,967
You said you have to go to the company anyway.

754
00:55:51,967 --> 00:55:55,633
That's me, but you should go where you want to visit.

755
00:55:55,633 --> 00:55:58,433
I'm curious about how my friend works.

756
00:55:58,433 --> 00:56:00,400
Is that not possible?

757
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:03,100
All right, let's go.

758
00:56:03,100 --> 00:56:07,400
But, can friends take the subway together?

759
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:08,920
Do what's comfortable.

760
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:11,060
Shall we part here and meet again later?

761
00:56:11,067 --> 00:56:12,733
It's fine.

762
00:56:20,633 --> 00:56:23,100
The subway in Seoul is incredibly complicated.

763
00:56:23,100 --> 00:56:25,233
Just follow me closely.

764
00:56:28,533 --> 00:56:31,133
- Why aren't you coming? 
 - It's convenient to transfer here.

765
00:56:31,133 --> 00:56:32,667
On 5-2.

766
00:56:40,767 --> 00:56:43,133
   

767
00:56:48,500 --> 00:56:50,300
Did you wait long?

768
00:56:50,867 --> 00:56:53,500
So this is where my friend works.

769
00:56:54,200 --> 00:56:57,033
You should have waited in the coffee shop on the first floor.

770
00:56:57,033 --> 00:56:59,633
It was fun watching people.

771
00:57:01,867 --> 00:57:04,467
Ah, I'm hungry.

772
00:57:04,467 --> 00:57:06,100
Shall we eat?

773
00:57:07,133 --> 00:57:09,433
Is it okay to eat alone with a friend?

774
00:57:09,433 --> 00:57:11,633
Then, should we eat separately?

775
00:57:11,633 --> 00:57:13,767
Let's eat and then meet up again.

776
00:57:45,900 --> 00:57:48,033
Hold this for me, please.

777
00:57:48,033 --> 00:57:49,867
No, I can't.

778
00:57:49,867 --> 00:57:51,233
What?

779
00:57:51,233 --> 00:57:53,367
Don't you know the perilla leaf debate?

780
00:57:54,233 --> 00:57:57,067
Han Woo has strictly defined friendships.

781
00:57:57,500 --> 00:57:59,933
But both of you have the same opinion.

782
00:57:59,933 --> 00:58:01,533
So, it's not possible.

783
00:58:02,167 --> 00:58:04,100
Got a death wish?

784
00:58:05,633 --> 00:58:08,933
You… Are you more afraid of Han Woo?

785
00:58:08,933 --> 00:58:11,000
Or are you more afraid of me?

786
00:58:37,233 --> 00:58:40,133
Hey, between friends, can you debone the fi…

787
00:58:41,500 --> 00:58:43,833
It must be delicious.

788
00:58:46,567 --> 00:58:51,733
I'm good at this because my knowledge of animals is extensive.

789
00:58:51,733 --> 00:58:53,767
Fish are vertebrates.

790
00:58:53,767 --> 00:58:56,800
This spine, that is where the backbone is located.

791
00:58:56,800 --> 00:58:59,567
And also this fin…

792
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:03,600
Eat.

793
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:05,300
